-------------------------
gnome-disk-utility 3.5.3
-------------------------

The gnome-disk-utility project provides the Disks application for
dealing with storage devices. It relies on the udisks project.

Changes since gnome-disk-utility 3.5.2:

David Zeuthen (39):
      Post-release version bump to 3.5.3
      about-dialog: use gnome-disks for the icon, not palimpsest
      Add back Benchmark dialog
      Show sample size and number of samples for benchmarks
      Add a settings dialog for power management and acoustic levels
      Make volume grid look right (grey, not blue) when selected and unfocused
      Add a "Wake-up from Standby" menu item
      Don't show WWN if we already show a serial
      Add erase option when formatting, show job progress and allow job cancelation
      Remove some "madness" from the Drive Settings dialog
      Don't show "standby timeout" setting for SSD drives
      Show estimated time remaining when a job is pending
      Rework UI for pending jobs
      Don't include SMART self-test percentage in one-liner summary
      Streamline time duration routines
      Use more sensible spacings in format disk and format volume dialogs
      Add support for ATA secure erase and non-cancelable jobs
      Show vendor recommended AAM level and use it as a default
      Don't allow standby on SSD drives
      Be a bit more precise in the warning dialog when formatting
      Add more compiler warnings
      Add more compiler warnings
      Properly initialize variable
      Don't define _FORTIFY_SOURCE
      Update compiler warning flags once again
      Don't show sub-minute precision for restoring/creating disk images
      Mark strings for translation
      Fix typo in previous commit
      Rescan device when we're done restoring a disk image onto it
      Handle partition setups with overlapping partitions
      Refine handling of overlapping partitions
      Show "Create Disk Image" even if free space on a drive is selected
      Fix 64-bit extension of integer
      Use GtkLevelBar widget for conveying passphrase strength
      disk-image-mounter: leave mounting to gnome-shell
      Port from libgnome-keyring-1 to libsecret-1
      Be a bit more careful when checking power state
      Nuke debug spew from last commit
      Update NEWS for release

Olav Vitters (1):
      MimeType key in gnome-disk-image-mounter.desktop must end on semicolon

Updated translations: Aurimas Černius, Chao-Hsiung Liao, Cheng Lu,
   Daniel Mustieles, Fran Diéguez, Ihar Hrachyshka, Kjartan Maraas,
   Milo Casagrande, Nilamdyuti Goswami, Piotr Drąg, Tom Tryfonidis,
   Yuri Kozlov, Мирослав Николић

David Zeuthen,
July 27, 2012

